cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on image recognition tasks and proposes a new model called Attention Branch Network (ABN) that introduces an attention mechanism for visual explanation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also discusses the training of the model in an end-to-end manner, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of attention mechanism for improving performance also indicates that it could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions facial attribute recognition, which suggests that it may belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as well as cs.MM (Multimedia).
